  "id": "crypto-go-operations-release",
  "courseId": "cryptography-go",
  "title": "Production Operations, Incidents, Recovery, and Release Defense",
  "description": "A release rotates keys and formats in one irreversible deployment, has no old-data corpus or rollback, monitors only errors, and discovers restore failure during an incident. Learners cumulatively produce cryptographic production defense and recovery drill through theory, guided work, debugging, transfer, retrieval, and assessment.",
  "order": 28,
  "objectives": [
    "Define low-cardinality success, reject, latency, work-factor, key-version, algorithm, expiry, rotation, migration, dependency, and recovery signals without secret leakage.",
    "Load-test entropy, CPU, memory-hard KDFs, HSM/KMS quotas, certificate services, revocation, key caches, queues, and degraded modes with bounded admission.",
    "Canary reader/writer, algorithm, key, format, certificate, and dependency changes with old/new matrices, dual-read boundaries, telemetry, and rollback."
